Usage: dt_xmouse MODE

Generates X mouse events from DiamondTouch table signals in one of
several modes. The following modes are available:

0 (DEFAULT)
  cursor follows finger, then clicks at end of motion
1 (MELS_CAFE)
  cursor leaps to finger-down position and clicks; no continuous motion
2 (PAINT)
  button down when finger is (but for noise); cursor follows (click & drag)
3 (WEB_DEMO)
  same as DEFAULT
4 (MOVE_ONLY)
  self explanatory; no button activity
5 (MAP_DEMO)
  same as PAINT, but without the noisy up/down during motion
6 (ANTI_NOISE)
  same as MAP_DEMO, but two fingers make a right-button drag
